HEADWORD: Sclerotium
<hw>Scle*ro"ti*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Sclerotia</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>sklhro`s</grk> hard.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A hardened body formed by certain fungi, as by the <spn>Claviceps
purpurea</spn>, which produces ergot.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The mature or resting stage of a
plasmodium.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sclerotome</ent>⟦br⟧
